document_data.History:
Daluth was one of the dreadspells sent with [[Elryn]] to find and slay a [[Chosen of Mystra]] near [[Westgate]] two tendays into the Chaos of [[the Art]] in the {{yearlink|797}}. During the first leg of the trip, he had [[Uldus Blackram]] lead the way, while a knife to the man's back. During the first leg of their trip, Uldus Blackram was killed by [[Ilbryn Starym]], an [[elven]] [[wizard]] they chanced upon.{{cite book/Elminster Ascending/The Temptation of Elminster|696-698|17}}

Once they found the ruin, Karsus' Keep, Daluth helped loot it of valuables.{{cite book/Elminster Ascending/The Temptation of Elminster|725-726|19}} Once their looted magic failed against Azuth, despite bringing down the ruin, they fled.{{cite book/Elminster Ascending/The Temptation of Elminster|730-731|19}}

When Dread Sister [[Klalaera]] appeared and herded them back against Azuth, they were stopped partway by [[Umbregard]] and [[Starsunder]], two mages that appeared suddenly. During the battle, after being injured by a beam that bared the flesh of his shoulder and the Dreadspells subsequently being reduced to just two, Daluth struck with a wand against Klalaera; upon death, her body to become animated by the power of Darklady [[Avroana]]. He was killed by a bolt of dark flame sprouting from her mouth, which left hardly anything of him.
